cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with object segmentation and annotation, which are core topics in computer vision. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel approach for semi-automatic annotation of object instances using a polygon prediction task, which involves the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs). 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques for object segmentation and annotation. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve natural language processing (NLP) techniques for human annotation of object instances. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is also less likely but possible as the paper may involve the use of graphics techniques for visualizing and manipulating polygon annotations.
